79:  \label{lem:cotangent_exact_structure}
80-  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.cotangentExactSeq_structure}
81-  \uses{def:cotangent_alpha, def:cotangent_beta}
82-  The composition $\beta \circ \alpha$ vanishes, the resulting short complex is exact at the middle term, and $\beta$ is an epimorphism. The three ingredients are local statements whose ring-level inputs are the exactness of the Mathlib cotangent sequence $\Omega_{A'/A} \otimes_{A'} B \to \Omega_{B/A} \to \Omega_{B/A'} \to 0$, together with the surjectivity of the right-hand map.
83-\end{lemma}
84-
85-\begin{proof}
86-  \uses{def:cotangent_alpha, def:cotangent_beta}
87-  We dispose of the three claims separately.
88-
89-  \emph{Vanishing $\beta \circ \alpha = 0$.} Inject through the adjunction
90-  $\mathrm{pullback}\,f \dashv \mathrm{pushforward}\,f$, naturality of which converts the equation into one in $Y.\mathrm{Modules}$ of the form $(\hom_{\mathrm{Adj}}\alpha) \cdot (\mathrm{pushforward}\,f).\mathrm{map}\,\beta = 0$. The left-hand side unfolds via the universal property of $\mathrm{relativeDifferentials}'\,\phi$ to a Derivation-valued equality; testing against the canonical derivation $\delta_{\phi}$ reduces the equation pointwise to ``the derivation $\delta_{\phi_2'}$ vanishes on the image of the morphism of presheaves $\phi_2$'', which is the defining property of $\delta_{\phi_2'}$. The composed-adjunction coherence required for the unfolding is the equality $\phi_g' \cdot f^c = \mathrm{unit}\,\phi_{fg}'$ (which is \texttt{rfl} at the Scheme level via $(f \cdot g).c = g.c \cdot \mathrm{pushforward}(g).\mathrm{map}\,f.c$).
91-
92:  \emph{Exactness at the middle.} Exactness of a short complex of sheaves of modules is detected stalkwise: a short complex is exact iff it is exact on every stalk. On each stalk we are reduced to the ring-level exactness $\Omega_{A'/A} \otimes_{A'} B \to \Omega_{B/A} \to \Omega_{B/A'} \to 0$ provided by Mathlib's \texttt{KaehlerDifferential.exact\_mapBaseChange\_map}. The stalkwise-exactness criterion is a small Mathlib-gap-fill (Lemma~\ref{lem:sheafOfModules_exact_iff_stalkwise} below).
93-
94:  \emph{Surjectivity of $\beta$.} Epimorphism is reflected through the faithful forgetful functor $\mathrm{SheafOfModules} \to \mathrm{PresheafOfModules}$: it suffices to show $\beta.\mathrm{val}$ is an epi of presheaves. The latter follows from \texttt{PresheafOfModules.epi\_iff\_surjective} together with \texttt{KaehlerDifferential.map\_surjective} on each open. The reflection step is a small Mathlib-gap-fill (Lemma~\ref{lem:sheafOfModules_epi_of_epi_presheaf} below).
95-\end{proof}
