124-\section{Smoothness and local freeness of $\Omega$}
125-
126-\begin{theorem}\leanok
127-[Smoothness in terms of $\Omega$]
128-  \label{thm:smooth_iff_locally_free_omega}
129-  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.smooth_iff_locally_free_omega}
130-  \uses{def:relative_kaehler_sheaf}
131-  Let $f \colon X \to S$ be a finite-presentation morphism of schemes. Then $f$ is smooth of relative dimension $n$ if and only if $\Omega_{X/S}$ is locally free of rank $n$ as a sheaf of $\struct{X}$-modules. The forward direction is the Jacobian criterion; the converse follows from the cotangent exact sequence and Nakayama's lemma applied at each point.
132-\end{theorem}
