146-\begin{theorem}\leanok
147-[Serre-duality genus equality]
148-  \label{thm:serre_duality_genus}
149-  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.serre_duality_genus}
150-  \uses{def:relative_kaehler_sheaf}
151-  Let $C$ be a smooth proper geometrically irreducible curve over a field $k$. Then
152-  \[
153-    \dim_k H^0(C, \Omega_{C/k}) \;=\; \dim_k H^1(C, \struct{C}).
154-  \]
155-  Both sides equal the genus $g(C)$. The equality is the dimension one case of Serre duality applied to the canonical sheaf; combined with the definition $g(C) = \dim_k H^1(C, \struct{C})$, this provides the alternative differential-theoretic characterisation used when computing the relative dimension of $\Jac(C)$ at the identity.
156-\end{theorem}

